<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 92 / Election 1992: Lead for Labour in marginals
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY MORETON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR appears to be taking votes from the Liberal Democrats in Wales and
pulling in front of the Conservatives in several marginal seats, Anthony
Moreton writes.
According to an NOP poll conducted for the television company HTV at the
weekend, Labour may take Delyn from the Conservatives and consolidate its
tenuous hold on Clwyd South West. In the south it was doing well in Cardiff
Central and Pembroke and looked likely to hold its by-election gains in
Monmouth and the Vale of Glamorgan.
The survey offers some comfort to the Conservatives because it indicates
that the party is increasing its support in seats where there is a three-way
split with Labour and Plaid Cymru, the Welsh nationalists.
</TEXT>
